# Node Version Manager

Before running any npm commands (e.g. `npm install`, `npm run`, `npm test`), ensure Node is available via nvm:

```bash
source ~/.nvm/nvm.sh && nvm use && npm <command>
```

Or when already in a shell with nvm loaded:

```bash
nvm use && npm <command>
```

The project has a `.nvmrc` file (Node 22). Running `nvm use` selects the correct Node version so npm commands succeed.
